#438

- Growing scattered on woodland duff in low mixed oak/hickory woodland near creek.
- Caps planoconvex, bald, whitish with a light tan central area. Cap margins with a slightly inrolled sterile tissue.
- Lamellae light tan, adnexed, crowded with frequent partial gills.
- Stipe whitish and fibrulose, turning slightly brownish in places.
- Mycelium aggressive on substrates.

Additional Details
- Spore Print: whitish almost pale tan/pink.
